correctness.rationale: The extraction is largely incorrect, mixes different materials, fabricates many parameters, and violates the schema in places. Key issues: (1) Material mismatch and mixing: aldSystem.materialDeposited is set to InGaZnO (IGZO), but most deviceProperties (μ_FE = 103.66 cm^2/V·s, SS = 96 mV/dec, Vth ≈ −0.94 V, I_ON/I_OFF ≈ 1.35×10^8) correspond to the optimized IGO (In:Ga = 4:1) device, not IGZO. supercycleDesign and aldMethod include Zn (IGZO) while the electrical performance is for IGO; filmComposition.atomicRatio is given as 4:1:1 (not reported) whereas the article reports IGO 4:1 (In:Ga) and IGZO 1:1:1 (In:Ga:Zn). crystallinity is set to polycrystalline while the extracted composition is IGZO; the article states the IGZO (this work) film is amorphous, and the polycrystalline result applies to IGO after 800 °C anneal. (2) Fabricated/untraceable parameters: growth-per-cycle (0.1 Å), numberofCycles (100), saturation (True), nucleationPeriod (5), dosingTime (100 ms), purgeTime (100 ms), precursor and coReactant flow rates (10 and 300 “SCM-PER-MIN”), uniformity (5%), conformality (AR 10), roughness (1.2 nm), filmDensity (5.5 g/dm^3), refractiveIndex (1.8), absorptionCoefficient (0.01), and optical characterization method (“Tauc plot”) are not reported anywhere in the article. coReactant “flow” of 300 contradicts the text, which gives ozone concentration (300 g m^-3), not a flow; only the purge Ar flow (100 sccm) is specified. (3) Incorrect or inconsistent process parameters: temperature 250 °C is the IGO deposition condition; no deposition temperature for IGZO is given. substrate is described as “p++-doped silicon wafer,” but the channel is deposited on an ONO stack on that wafer (lack of precision). (4) Film-level electrical properties incorrect: materialProperties.electricalProperties.mobility is labeled as measured by Hall but the value 103.66 cm^2/V·s is the field-effect mobility from FETs; reported Hall mobility for IGO at 800 °C is ≈107.84 cm^2/V·s. carrierDensity uses unit C-PER-M3 and a value (4.58e17) that is orders of magnitude off relative to the article’s cm^-3 values (e.g., ~3.31×10^17 cm^-3 ≈ 3.31×10^23 m^-3); unit should be PER-M3 with correct conversion. Resistivity value is not clearly traceable given the garbled ranges in the text. (5) Schema violations: processParameters.plasmaPower is set to null but must be an object or omitted (Thermal ALD should omit it). thicknessControl.growthPerCycle incorrectly contains a filmThickness property (not allowed; growthPerCycle allows only ‘values’). filmThickness is also duplicated at the thicknessControl level and inside growthPerCycle. (6) Supercycle design not supported: numberofSubcycles = 1 for each compound and subcycleSequence given without evidence in the article. Corrections needed: choose a single process per record (IGO or IGZO) and align all fields; if IGO, set materialDeposited to IGO, remove Zn-related entries, use In:Ga = 4:1, deposition 250 °C, pressure 300 mTorr, ozone co-reactant, Ar purge 100 sccm, thickness 10 nm, deviceProperties as reported; use Hall mobility and carrier density with correct units and values. If IGZO, use In:Ga:Zn = 1:1:1, keep IGZO-specific crystallinity (amorphous), and only include parameters reported. Remove or leave out all unreported parameters (GPC, cycles, dosing/purge times, precursor/co-reactant flows, optical constants, uniformity, conformality, roughness, density). Fix schema issues by omitting plasmaPower for TALD and removing filmThickness from growthPerCycle.

completeness.rationale: Largely incomplete/misaligned with the article and several schema issues. Key problems: (1) Wrong or conflated process: the article reports ALD of IGO (In:Ga supercycle, 4:1 optimized) and also IGZO (1:1:1) as a comparison, but the extraction provides a single process labeled InGaZnO while device/electrical values correspond to IGO; multiple distinct processes (IGO and IGZO) are missing. (2) Supercycle design not grounded: counts set to 1:1:1 without mapping to the reported IGO 4:1 or IGZO 1:1:1 ratios; no subcycle design for the IGO cases. (3) Many process parameters are fabricated/not traceable: GPC (0.1 Å), number of cycles (100), nucleation period (5 cycles), dosing/purge times (100 ms), co-reactant and precursor flow rates (sccm) and carrier gas assignment are not reported in the article (only purge Ar 100 sccm and ozone concentration 300 g m−3 are given). (4) Schema violation: plasmaPower is present with null, but the schema expects an object if provided; omit if not used. (5) Material properties not supported: optical properties (n, absorption, band gap via Tauc) and roughness, density, uniformity, conformality have no measurements in the article. (6) Film composition errors: claims XPS elemental concentration/atomic ratio and sets ‘4:1:1’ for In:Ga:Zn, which is incorrect (IGO has no Zn; IGZO is 1:1:1); XPS was not reported. (7) Electrical property inconsistencies and unit issues: material carrier density uses C-PER-M3 with an incorrect magnitude; mobility labeled as Hall but value (103.66 cm2/Vs) corresponds to device field-effect mobility; crystallinity set to polycrystalline while IGZO in this work is amorphous. (8) Some values are correct but mixed contextually (e.g., pressure 300 mTorr, substrate p++ Si, post-annealed IGO device metrics), yet the overall process object is not a coherent, traceable ALD IGZO/IGO process per the article. To improve: add separate processes for IGO (with In:Ga = 4:1, deposition at 250 °C, 300 mTorr, Ar purge 100 sccm, ozone reactant) and IGZO (In:Ga:Zn = 1:1:1); remove or correct unreported GPC/times/flows; fix film composition and crystallinity to match each film; correct electrical property units/sources; and omit plasmaPower if not used.
